node.text: But seriously, All jokes aside, the new Wick Game Bag Brief is going to change your world. Aerowool Wick 150 Merino with 37.5 active particles means these bad boys breath like a champ, while the biometrically supportive design keeps everything in place. And with a generous mid length leg, you won’t have to worry about the Game Bag Brief riding up. Grab yours today at the link in my bio. @firstlitehunting #fueledbynature

node.text: We're expanding @wildandwhole, which was founded by our very own @danielleprewett, and launching its new website. To celebrate, I threw down with Danielle and @chefkevingillespie on a hot tip off. The problem is that The Flip Flop Flesher screwed it all up when he rendered his judgment. Help me identify the true winner. (That’s me!) You can check out the new site at the link in my bio. #fueledbynature 🎥 by @signs_west

node.text: with master call maker and all around solid fella, Jason Phelps. I’m proud of the results. These are high quality calls that are easy to get good, consistent results from. You will not be disappointed if you put your faith in us on this purchase. @phelpsgamecalls never makes a bad product. These are not exceptions.  Most of the stuff sold out immediately, but more is coming. Check out the full lineup at the link in my bio. #fueledbynature

node.text: #fueledbynature

node.title: This is what’s called a caustic work environment.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Steven Rinella on September 02, 2021. May be an image of outdoors.

node.text:
The guy who sent us this photo says they've "been having a great horned owl issue. 📸 @whaley_outdoors 
#fueledbynature

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Steven Rinella on September 01, 2021. May be an image of indoor and text that says '一'.

node.text: All of my bear rugs have been mounted with that open-mouthed growl. But @janis_putelis has pointed out that most bears you see aren’t growling at you, so why are they all mounted like that? Eventually I learned that bears aren’t done with a closed mouth because it’s a bitch for the taxidermist to get it right. I had this one done by @hayestaxidermystudio and they really nailed it. #fueledbynature
Das Boat Season 3 is here, folks. For this round, we head to the Northeast with @joe.cermele138 taking over as captain of the series. Grab your life jackets and some popcorn! #fueledbynature

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Steven Rinella on August 30, 2021. May be an image of outdoors.

node.text:
After decades of anticipation, it’s finally here folks. The F*cked-Up Old Deer Stands calendar is live and for sale. If we can’t sell this out, my career here at MeatEater is in jeopardy. Help a fella out and order a few at the link in my bio. 
#fueledbynature

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Steven Rinella on August 28, 2021. May be an image of 2 people and nature.

node.text: Got onto a pair of wolves while we were hunting dall sheep in Alaska. For a moment, it looked like I'd be doing a wolf episode of Pardon My Plate with @spencerneuharth, but they ended up giving me the slip and we never caught up to them again. Photo by @signs_west

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Steven Rinella on August 27, 2021. May be an image of 1 person, standing and nature.

node.text:
Recently, my daughter's friend commented that she doesn't eat fish. My daughter said, "Well, you'd hate our cabin!"
#fueledbynature

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Steven Rinella on August 26, 2021. May be an image of outdoors.

node.text:
Desert bighorn found by @michaelcurrierbjj in the Superstition Mountains of Arizona.
#meateater #fueledbynature

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Steven Rinella on August 24, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'PLEASE Do not bathe in the sinks Showers are avalible down at the aSnowshoe Motel They provide towel and if desired soap as well Shampo Please do not use this sink to wash dishes Please use sink up front by coffee machine. Thank you!'.

node.text: Rules, rules, rules!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Steven Rinella on August 21, 2021. May be an image of 1 person, standing and body of water.

node.text: My 11-year-old is so dedicated to spearfishing that he breathes through his snorkel even on dry land. #fueledbynature

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Steven Rinella on August 19, 2021. May be an image of child and outdoors.

node.text: My son and my nephew, filleting bait-sized pile perch. They served them fried on top of tortilla chips with a splash of jarred salsa. #fueledbynature

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Steven Rinella on August 17, 2021. May be an image of body of water and nature.

node.text: A fella from Alaska sent this image of how he found his boat after anchoring in some sheltered water. It swung in an unexpected direction and got stuck on that rock when the tide fell. Looks like some sort of installation art. #fueledbynature

node.text: Here's the most important unboxing video you'll ever see. Soon you'll be able to join us in a celebration of those fucked up old deer stands that we all know and love. We got about 1400 submissions from our audience, and whittled it down to twelve of our favorites for this 2022 calendar. We'll have it on sale soon. I think these suckers are gonna sell out in a hurry. If so, we'll know that we have the necessary support to move on to my dream, a fine art coffee table book featuring crazy deer stands from around the country. Stay tuned for another announcement when we're ready to ship. #fueledbynature
